- Yeah?
- Yeah.

21:19.677 --> 21:22.976
He says he doesn't
miss New York at all.

21:23.014 --> 21:24.845
I knew he'd bail.

21:24.882 --> 21:27.976
He was always way too much of a wimp
to stay here forever.

21:28.019 --> 21:30.010
- Do you want to know what I want?
- Hmm?

21:30.054 --> 21:33.922
- An omelet.
- Oh, wait. I'm just curious.

21:33.958 --> 21:38.224
Why do you hate
Los Angeles so much?

21:38.262 --> 21:40.526
Because it's the epicenter
of all that is awful.

21:43.067 --> 21:45.467
- Wait.
- Feed me.

21:45.503 --> 21:48.472
Dave told me this awesome thing
about LA. No, listen.

21:48.506 --> 21:51.669
He says the whole town
is like this blank canvas,

21:51.709 --> 21:55.668
and whatever you bring to it...
that's what it is.

21:55.713 --> 21:58.978
It's just this random collection
of neighborhoods where it's always sunny

21:59.016 --> 22:02.975
and it basically reflects
wherever you're at back at you.

22:03.020 --> 22:05.454
So if you're happy, LA is great.

22:05.490 --> 22:07.515
If you're not, LA sucks.

22:07.558 --> 22:10.026
But it has nothing to do
with Los Angeles

22:10.061 --> 22:12.962
because... get this...

22:12.997 --> 22:15.192
there's no such thing.

22:17.368 --> 22:19.859
And?

22:19.904 --> 22:22.031
And that's it.

22:23.841 --> 22:28.175
If you don't feed me soon,
I'm going to eat your face.

22:28.212 --> 22:30.203
Let's go.

22:39.157 --> 22:42.957
Okay, what's going on?

22:42.994 --> 22:45.360
Dave said what?

22:45.396 --> 22:50.265
He wants to partner
with me, 50/50.

22:50.301 --> 22:53.395
But...

22:53.437 --> 22:57.237
we'd have to be out there.

22:58.643 --> 23:00.873
When?

23:00.912 --> 23:03.972
End of the month.

23:04.015 --> 23:06.006
And you want to do it?

23:31.509 --> 23:36.446
What I'm missing, I think,
is a great subject.

23:36.480 --> 23:40.473
Like... like the novel,
that which is new, you know?

23:40.518 --> 23:44.284
Where's my...
what do I draw upon?

23:45.456 --> 23:47.856
- I don't know.
- Exactly.

23:47.892 --> 23:49.951
I mean my great shame
as a writer

23:49.994 --> 23:53.657
is that I'm just this suburban kid
with good parents.

23:53.698 --> 23:57.395
You know,
I was fed, clothed,

23:57.435 --> 24:00.427
carpooled...
hardly Dickensian.

24:00.471 --> 24:02.939
- You know what I'm saying?
- Totally.

24:02.974 --> 24:05.568
I mean you...
with your situation...

24:05.610 --> 24:07.100
That's a gold mine.

24:07.144 --> 24:09.840
You got, like, tons of material

24:09.881 --> 24:13.442
all at the ripe old age
of whatever.

24:13.484 --> 24:16.351
How old are you anyway?

24:16.387 --> 24:18.787
I don't know.

24:18.823 --> 24:20.484
You don't know how old you are?

24:23.094 --> 24:25.255
When's your birthday?

24:39.810 --> 24:41.641
What are you so afraid of?

24:43.281 --> 24:46.409
I'm afraid my brain
is going to melt.

24:46.450 --> 24:49.476
I'm afraid we will never
walk anywhere ever again.

24:49.520 --> 24:53.115
I'm afraid we won't care
about things anymore

24:53.157 --> 24:56.558
except opening
weekend grosses

24:56.594 --> 24:59.324
and Pilates classes.

24:59.363 --> 25:02.855
Yeah, but you know they'd be,
like, the best Pilates classes.

25:02.900 --> 25:05.061
There's no art there.

25:05.102 --> 25:07.400
- That's ridiculous.
- They have no culture.

25:07.438 --> 25:09.269
New York has everything...

25:09.307 --> 25:12.538
the best restaurants,
best theater, museums...

25:12.576 --> 25:15.374
Right, and how many museums
do you go to in an average week?

25:15.413 --> 25:17.040
- I'm just curious.
- That is not the point.

25:17.081 --> 25:18.446
- Yes, that is the point.
- Not the point.

25:18.482 --> 25:19.972
I mean, what good is paying
out the nose to live here

25:20.017 --> 25:21.609
if we never
take advantage of it?

25:21.652 --> 25:24.314
We might as well live somewhere else
and just visit every once in a while

25:24.355 --> 25:25.845
and actually do things.

25:25.890 --> 25:28.484
You know, hit the Met,
take in a Broadway show,

25:28.526 --> 25:30.255
Carnegie Deli.

25:30.294 --> 25:32.694
"Wow, that's a really big sandwich.

25:32.730 --> 25:35.130
- I don't know if I can eat all that."
- I love New York.

25:35.166 --> 25:36.724
You're miserable more than not.

25:36.767 --> 25:39.827
Yes, but that is not
New York's fault.

25:42.907 --> 25:44.898
New York is...

25:46.444 --> 25:48.435
What?

25:50.815 --> 25:53.215
...home.

25:53.250 --> 25:55.514
You're asking me to leave home.

26:06.097 --> 26:07.758
You know this is my job,
don't you?

26:07.798 --> 26:09.493
I have to sit here and write things.

26:09.533 --> 26:11.933
It's... it's not easy
with you staring at me.

26:23.247 --> 26:26.045
Sorry I don't have a television.

26:27.351 --> 26:28.841
What's your thing?
What do you like?

26:28.886 --> 26:31.286
You like art, huh?
You like to draw?

26:31.322 --> 26:33.654
Really?

26:35.359 --> 26:38.294
Here, draw yourself a television.

26:49.940 --> 26:52.932
#So I have under two minutes
to sing you this song #

26:52.977 --> 26:56.003
#It's quite the challenge actually
because I've loved you so long #

26:56.047 --> 26:58.948
#And I know I'm always writing
so you think I'm good with words #

26:58.983 --> 27:02.077
#But I can hardly express
how I feel #

27:02.119 --> 27:05.020
#'Cause words aren't why
love is real #

27:05.056 --> 27:09.015
#And I don't know why
I love you, I just do #

27:10.561 --> 27:13.621
#There was a message in a bottle
at the bottom of the sea #

27:13.664 --> 27:16.758
#Somebody mistook rock
for paper accidenta-dentally #

27:16.801 --> 27:19.668
#So their letter never made it
to the lover they adore #

27:19.703 --> 27:22.672
#I had to fish it
from the ocean floor #

27:22.706 --> 27:25.800
#And I know you won't believe me,
but I swear to God it's true #

27:25.843 --> 27:28.607
#The letter said "I love you,
but I don't know why I do" #

27:28.646 --> 27:31.706
#That's exactly when it hit me,
that's exactly how I feel #

27:31.749 --> 27:35.048
#'Cause though
my love is real... #

27:35.086 --> 27:36.815
Amazing, right?

27:36.854 --> 27:38.378
Are you sure
you don't like these

27:38.422 --> 27:40.287
just because they're
a lot of pictures of you?

27:40.324 --> 27:41.814
No.

27:41.859 --> 27:45.226
But I do look
incredibly handsome

27:45.262 --> 27:46.786
in this one.

27:46.831 --> 27:48.389
Look at me.

27:48.432 --> 27:50.662
I'm like a dashing
Russian aristocrat.

27:50.701 --> 27:52.328
Oh.

27:54.038 --> 27:55.869
What do you think
was going on?

27:55.906 --> 27:57.931
I don't know.
Something bad.

27:57.975 --> 28:00.409
He says he won't go back.

28:01.512 --> 28:05.278
Well, he's supercute.
I say we keep him.

28:05.316 --> 28:07.807
I'm kidding.
We can't keep him.

28:07.852 --> 28:10.980
- Sam, don't keep him.
- I'm not keeping him.

28:11.021 --> 28:13.012
Calm down.

28:24.101 --> 28:27.434
Sorry about the ball.
It's all I got.

28:40.084 --> 28:42.075
Hello?

28:45.389 --> 28:47.653
Okay.

28:47.691 --> 28:50.091
No, it's not like I didn't
see this one coming.

28:51.962 --> 28:54.328
So that's the last of them, huh?

28:56.500 --> 29:00.732
No, I'm, uh... I'm fine.
Thanks.

29:19.390 --> 29:22.450
Did you know that my three
most financially successful years

29:22.493 --> 29:25.087
in New York City
were when I was dealing pot?

29:27.431 --> 29:29.899
You don't need Dave
or some crappy town

29:29.934 --> 29:31.424
to do something great.

29:31.468 --> 29:35.302
- I believe in you.
- Why?

29:35.339 --> 29:37.967
'Cause you're my man.

29:38.008 --> 29:41.569
You're my big, funny,
floppy-haired man.

29:42.680 --> 29:46.480
We don't need to know everything
in advance, okay?

29:46.517 --> 29:50.886
You'll figure out your thing
and we'll have money eventually.

29:50.921 --> 29:52.411
That's how it works.

29:52.456 --> 29:54.856
No, not here.

29:54.892 --> 29:56.587
Not always.

29:58.729 --> 30:02.358
I just want to feel like the crap
I put myself through is...

30:05.369 --> 30:07.200
I don't know.

30:07.238 --> 30:09.297
No no, yeah, I did.
I called him yesterday.

30:11.242 --> 30:13.403
I'm just tired.

30:23.554 --> 30:26.352
- Oh.
- Sorry.

30:26.390 --> 30:29.689
So I'm... I'm generally not
a happy hour kind of guy,

30:29.727 --> 30:33.424
- but I thought you might like...
- Oh, uh, yeah sorry. I can't.

30:33.464 --> 30:35.125
- It's a school night.
- Oh, yeah.

30:35.165 --> 30:37.156
- Bye.
- Okay, bye.

30:37.201 --> 30:40.466
Oh. Two ships, two ships.

30:40.504 --> 30:42.665
- Hey, Beth.
- Hey.

31:38.562 --> 31:41.292
- What?
- What do you mean?

31:41.332 --> 31:43.027
Why did you want
to see me so bad?

31:43.067 --> 31:45.058
I just... does there have
to be a reason?

31:47.271 --> 31:49.136
I don't know.

31:49.173 --> 31:51.107
I still...

31:53.477 --> 31:55.536
Whatever.
It's just been a while.

31:55.579 --> 31:58.912
Have a drink with me.
Please?

32:28.379 --> 32:29.368
- She hated me.
- Not true.

32:29.413 --> 32:31.313
- She hated me.
- She didn't hate you.

32:31.348 --> 32:33.043
She just thought
you needed a haircut.

32:33.083 --> 32:35.142
Yeah well, I couldn't have been
nicer to that woman.

32:35.185 --> 32:39.485
I... I brought her flowers.
I even tucked my shirt in.

32:39.523 --> 32:41.957
Wow, shocking that
that didn't win her over.

32:41.992 --> 32:44.222
- Nothing would have.
- I'm her daughter.

32:44.261 --> 32:45.853
She didn't want me to get hurt.

32:45.896 --> 32:48.456
But I guess in fairness, you know,
she was wrong about you.

32:48.499 --> 32:51.024
Oh no, wait.
She was totally right.

32:51.068 --> 32:54.401
- Come on.
- Mothers are always right.

32:54.438 --> 32:56.099
I fuckin' hate that.

32:58.942 --> 33:02.969
I can handle your mother
hating me.

33:03.013 --> 33:05.447
I can't stand the thought
that you hate me.

33:17.528 --> 33:20.497
- Hey.
- Hey.

33:20.531 --> 33:23.694
- You're back.
- A man of my word.

33:23.734 --> 33:25.725
- Mississippi.
- Sam.

33:25.769 --> 33:31.537
- M-I-S-S-I-S-S-I-P-P-I?
- Very good.

33:31.575 --> 33:33.805
- How's your little brother?
- Who?

33:33.844 --> 33:35.937
- The kid?
- Oh, good.

33:35.979 --> 33:37.469
Yeah yeah yeah yeah.
He's good.

33:37.514 --> 33:38.674
Well, it's great that you do that.

33:38.715 --> 33:41.377
You know, you're...
you're really good at your job.

33:41.418 --> 33:43.318
- Am I?
- Yeah, I've been...

33:43.353 --> 33:45.344
I've been watching you
do your thing.

33:45.389 --> 33:47.857
- You're good.
- Wow.

33:47.891 --> 33:50.121
I must be a really good actress

33:50.160 --> 33:52.424
because I fucking hate my job.

33:52.463 --> 33:54.124
- You're an actress?
- No.

33:54.164 --> 33:55.392
What do you do
when you're not here?

33:55.432 --> 33:57.730
- I sing.
- Sing? Songs?

33:57.768 --> 34:01.636
- Yeah, songs. Cabaret.
- Ah.

34:01.672 --> 34:03.936
- What do you do?
- I write.

34:03.974 --> 34:07.000
- Words?
- Yeah, words.

34:09.246 --> 34:11.271
So you sing.
Are you... you any good?

34:11.315 --> 34:13.612
Well, you come listen
and then tell me.

34:13.650 --> 34:16.083
No, I... I could never
come hear you sing.

34:16.119 --> 34:19.246
- Why not?
- Because I like you.

34:19.289 --> 34:20.880
That makes no sense.

34:30.000 --> 34:32.127
You happy to see me?

34:32.168 --> 34:34.159
I don't know yet.

34:44.848 --> 34:46.907
This is bad.

34:46.949 --> 34:49.214
I have to work in the morning.

34:49.253 --> 34:51.949
- Some people work.
- Hey, I work.

34:51.989 --> 34:54.753
Playing bass in a shitty band

34:54.791 --> 34:58.318
and considering applying
to grad school is not a job.

34:58.362 --> 35:00.023
You think the band is shitty?

35:02.266 --> 35:04.734
Well, you were front row
at every show.

35:04.768 --> 35:06.759
I was your girlfriend.

35:06.803 --> 35:10.762
That, like, contractually obligated me
to be a groupie.

35:10.807 --> 35:14.402
Yeah, but you always...

35:14.444 --> 35:17.538
you just looked like you were
enjoying yourself, that's all.

35:24.555 --> 35:27.456
I was.

35:27.491 --> 35:29.482
I did.

35:34.965 --> 35:37.433
All right, let's do this.
Tell me things.

35:37.467 --> 35:40.163
When, Mississippi,
did you leave Mississippi

35:40.203 --> 35:41.534
and come to New York City?

35:41.572 --> 35:43.096
- When I was 17.
- Oh great.

35:43.140 --> 35:44.732
So you've been here,
what, two years?

35:44.775 --> 35:48.006
- Aw, nice.
- Ooh wait, where's your accent?

35:48.045 --> 35:49.603
Oh, it's here...

35:49.646 --> 35:51.876
when I need it.

35:51.915 --> 35:53.212
Drink this.

35:53.250 --> 35:56.117
Yes, ma'am.
Cheers.

35:56.153 --> 35:58.144
Mm!

35:58.188 --> 35:59.849
What the fuck, man?

35:59.890 --> 36:01.653
Why won't you come
hear me sing?

36:01.692 --> 36:04.183
- You really want to know?
- Yeah.

36:04.227 --> 36:06.127
Because I once dated
this girl in college

36:06.163 --> 36:07.653
who desperately wanted
to be an actress.

36:07.698 --> 36:09.222
I mean it was all she talked about.

36:09.266 --> 36:12.326
And I finally went
to see her in this play.

36:12.369 --> 36:13.529
Bad?

36:13.570 --> 36:17.438
So unburdened with talent
it was amazing.

36:17.474 --> 36:20.534
- I mean I had to break up with her.
- Because she was a bad actress?

36:20.577 --> 36:22.067
No, I didn't care
if she was good or not.

36:22.112 --> 36:24.740
It was... she so believed she was good
and it made me feel like,

36:24.781 --> 36:28.478
wow, this girl doesn't
know herself at all.

36:28.518 --> 36:31.646
And I think you're terrific.
I do.

36:31.688 --> 36:33.178
Therefore, I could never
come hear you sing

36:33.223 --> 36:35.157
because it'll change everything
if I learn you can't.

36:35.192 --> 36:37.023
- What if I'm amazing?
- What if you aren't?

36:37.060 --> 36:39.392
- What if you suck as a writer?
- I don't.

36:39.429 --> 36:43.365
Whoa, you are bad news.

36:49.873 --> 36:53.365
Sammy, I'm calling you
because you're my sponsor

36:53.410 --> 36:55.605
and I'm about to fall
off the wagon.

36:55.646 --> 36:58.581
It happens, right?
Don't be mad.

36:58.615 --> 37:00.776
Okay, I'm going to take
your not picking up to mean

37:00.817 --> 37:03.012
that the universe wants me
to fuck up badly right now.

37:03.053 --> 37:05.453
I'll call you tomorrow
and confess.

37:17.167 --> 37:19.158
Fuck!

37:36.787 --> 37:38.448
What's wrong?

37:38.488 --> 37:42.891
- I got bad news today.
- What?

37:42.926 --> 37:45.588
I'm a fuckin' failure.

37:45.629 --> 37:47.290
Aw.

37:47.330 --> 37:51.061
Fuck, I was impressive once.

37:51.101 --> 37:53.763
I'm telling you,

37:53.804 --> 37:56.898
parent-teacher conferences
back in the day...

37:56.940 --> 37:58.931
I was unstoppable.

37:58.975 --> 38:01.273
- Little Sammy Wexler.
- I'll bet you were.

38:01.311 --> 38:02.801
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

38:13.090 --> 38:15.320
It's okay to not
say anything, right?

38:15.358 --> 38:19.192
I always want to...
I always want to talk.

38:19.229 --> 38:22.858
I don't always have to be talking.

38:25.335 --> 38:27.599
You gotta stop me
because I'm just gonna keep...

38:27.637 --> 38:30.970
I'm just gonna keep going.
I don't know how those things...

38:47.524 --> 38:50.425
Shh.

38:59.202 --> 39:01.193
This way. Come.

39:01.238 --> 39:02.728
Wait wait, shh!

39:02.773 --> 39:05.606
Listen, there might be
a small black child

39:05.642 --> 39:07.405
sleeping on my couch,
so we have to be quiet.

39:07.444 --> 39:08.934
Might?

39:08.979 --> 39:10.469
There's definitely
a small black child

39:10.514 --> 39:12.038
sleeping on my couch,
so we have to be quiet.

39:12.082 --> 39:14.380
Okay.

39:14.417 --> 39:16.749
Shh shh!

39:16.787 --> 39:19.187
- Look look, it's my bedroom.
- Oh.

39:19.222 --> 39:21.952
- How nice is it in here?
- Amazing.

39:25.662 --> 39:28.460
- Hey.
- Hey. What?

39:28.498 --> 39:31.058
- I'm not going to sleep with you.
- Sure you are.

39:31.101 --> 39:35.060
- No, I can't.
- Come on, that's defeatist.

39:35.105 --> 39:37.232
You can do anything
you set your mind to.

39:37.274 --> 39:39.242
Ow!

39:39.276 --> 39:40.834
- Shh!
- Ah.

39:40.877 --> 39:43.539
- The children.
- Oh.

39:44.748 --> 39:47.581
- Does he stay with you a lot?
- Well, occasionally.

39:47.617 --> 39:50.950
You know, rough home life.

39:50.987 --> 39:53.922
Sam, I'm serious.
I'm not going to sleep with you.

39:55.492 --> 39:57.255
Does this have something
to do with Jesus?

39:57.294 --> 40:00.195
- Is that what this is?
- No.

40:00.230 --> 40:03.358
- I made a New Year's resolution.
- To what?

40:03.400 --> 40:05.960
To not be such a whore.

40:06.002 --> 40:08.562
How's that been going for you?

40:08.605 --> 40:10.630
Well...

40:10.674 --> 40:13.108
- Come on.
- No no no no, I barely know you.

40:13.143 --> 40:15.703
All I know is you've got all these
sort of idiotic theories, okay?

40:15.745 --> 40:18.407
I'm not going to spend
the night with you.

40:18.448 --> 40:21.417
Okay, fine. I don't...

40:21.451 --> 40:23.442
I don't think you should spend
the night with me either.

40:23.486 --> 40:26.421
You don't?

40:26.456 --> 40:28.924
I think you should spend
the next three nights with me.

40:28.959 --> 40:32.656
- What?
- I'm serious!

40:32.696 --> 40:34.527
Stay with me.
Three days.

40:34.564 --> 40:36.828
I've got an extra set of keys.
You come and go as you please.

40:36.867 --> 40:39.165
I knew that last shot
was a bad idea.

40:39.202 --> 40:41.261
What? Come on.
This will be awesome.

40:41.304 --> 40:45.570
Look, I totally agree...
one-night stands are the worst.

40:45.609 --> 40:47.600
So you want to have
a three-night stand?

40:47.644 --> 40:48.804
Yeah.

40:48.845 --> 40:50.403
What is this,
like your line or something?

40:50.447 --> 40:52.176
No.

40:52.215 --> 40:54.581
You've said that
to other girls before!

40:54.618 --> 40:57.746
I've never even thought this before,
but it's totally genius, isn't it?

40:57.787 --> 41:00.517
No, it's like the worst idea ever.

41:00.557 --> 41:03.993
Hey hey hey, you stay here
for three days.

41:04.027 --> 41:06.154
Who knows what could happen?

41:06.196 --> 41:07.788
We sleep together once...
let's be honest,

41:07.831 --> 41:09.992
the odds are I'm never
gonna call you.

41:10.033 --> 41:12.024
You just said that out loud.

41:12.068 --> 41:14.229
Come on. Come on!

41:14.271 --> 41:16.671
- No way.
- Move in with me for three days.

41:16.706 --> 41:19.197
My mother warned me
about guys like you.

41:19.242 --> 41:23.144
Seriously.
It'll be an adventure, huh?

41:23.179 --> 41:25.010
We'll cook.

41:25.048 --> 41:27.642
We'll make
obscene amounts of love.

41:27.684 --> 41:29.811
We'll play with the adorable kid
on the couch

41:29.853 --> 41:32.151
