Hold on.
I have some, uh...

55:01.130 --> 55:02.495
It's okay, honey.

55:04.400 --> 55:07.392
Hey, um, can you...

55:07.436 --> 55:09.495
I'm not good with blood.

55:12.074 --> 55:13.939
Congratulations, Sam.

55:13.976 --> 55:17.605
You've just become the most
unattractive man in the world.

56:15.070 --> 56:18.301
Hey. Hey hey hey.

56:18.340 --> 56:19.898
- You're really leaving?
- Yeah.

56:19.942 --> 56:21.432
- Why?
- I'm not a babysitter.

56:21.477 --> 56:24.378
- He's totally mellow. You...
- I was talking about you.

56:26.982 --> 56:29.542
You have to let someone
know where he is.

56:29.585 --> 56:31.416
- I will.
- Today.

56:31.453 --> 56:33.717
- He's...
- He's a child.

56:38.761 --> 56:41.855
I can't get involved with this
right now, Sam.

56:41.897 --> 56:44.866
I'm trying to get my life together,
not fuck it up more.

56:44.900 --> 56:48.597
Look, I'm sorry that I lied to you.

56:48.637 --> 56:50.798
I'm a good person.

56:50.840 --> 56:53.570
- I'm trying to do the right thing here.
- You're going to take care of him?

56:53.609 --> 56:56.510
- For now, until I can...
- You're a mess.

56:57.880 --> 57:01.247
What, you don't need a project?

57:06.488 --> 57:08.353
I'm a mess too.

57:08.390 --> 57:10.381
Trust me.

57:12.328 --> 57:15.161
So let's...

57:15.197 --> 57:17.563
let's clean each other up.

57:21.837 --> 57:23.828
Bye, Sam.

57:57.740 --> 58:00.106
Sam.

58:00.142 --> 58:03.112
Come home soon.

58:04.413 --> 58:06.904
Sorry.

58:06.949 --> 58:09.179
- Hey.
- Are you crazy?

58:09.218 --> 58:11.812
- Why is he still with you?
- I'm helping him.

58:11.854 --> 58:14.322
Well, I talked to my friend Jill,
who's a social worker,

58:14.356 --> 58:17.154
and according to New York state law,
you've kidnapped him.

58:17.192 --> 58:20.389
Are you okay?
Do you miss your family?

58:20.429 --> 58:21.987
Is he feeding you?

58:22.031 --> 58:23.760
- What are you eating?
- Don't answer that.

58:23.799 --> 58:27.326
Look, I get that this is
killer material for a novel.

58:27.369 --> 58:30.964
Sensitive white guy learns life lessons
by taking in small black...

58:31.006 --> 58:34.806
- You actually think that I'm...
- Are you writing about him, Sam?

58:34.843 --> 58:36.902
This is a big deal.

58:36.946 --> 58:40.438
You can't just keep him.
He's not a goldfish.

58:40.482 --> 58:43.212
You need to let someone
know where he is.

58:44.687 --> 58:46.678
Look at these.

58:50.826 --> 58:52.817
I'm anxious to see
what will happen

58:52.861 --> 58:55.830
if I give him more than two pens
and a highlighter.

59:02.071 --> 59:04.062
Come on.

59:11.447 --> 59:13.881
Please fix this.
Your mom would be so upset.

59:13.916 --> 59:17.010
And then she's going to call my mom
and my mom's going to call me,

59:17.052 --> 59:19.020
and I don't have the energy.

59:19.054 --> 59:22.820
It's okay.
I'm on it, I promise.

59:22.858 --> 59:25.418
Okay.

59:25.461 --> 59:27.156
- I think you're good.
- Great.

59:27.196 --> 59:29.426
- Hey, Rasheen, say thank you.
- Thank you.

59:31.500 --> 59:33.968
Thank you.

59:34.003 --> 59:36.164
Come on, let's go.

59:36.205 --> 59:38.196
- Hey, Sam.
- Yep?

59:39.842 --> 59:42.811
- You've spent time in Los Angeles.
- Yeah.

59:42.845 --> 59:45.109
- Do you like it?
- It's okay.

59:45.147 --> 59:47.342
Would you ever want
to live there?

59:47.383 --> 59:49.715
No. Okay.

59:49.752 --> 59:51.242
Come on.

01:00:03.265 --> 01:00:05.256
Go.

01:00:14.076 --> 01:00:17.273
People shouldn't be able
to give him so much shit.

01:00:17.312 --> 01:00:20.440
The man's made
some of the best movies of all time.

01:00:20.482 --> 01:00:22.507
He just makes too many of them.

01:00:22.551 --> 01:00:26.419
One every year?
Why not one every other year?

01:00:26.455 --> 01:00:29.151
Take some time off
to recharge,

01:00:29.191 --> 01:00:35.152
spend a little quality time
with the wife-slash-daughter.

01:00:35.197 --> 01:00:37.392
Get out there,

01:00:37.433 --> 01:00:41.836
live a little, you know?

01:00:41.870 --> 01:00:44.737
- Marry me.
- What?

01:00:44.773 --> 01:00:47.867
- Let's get married.
- What?

01:00:47.910 --> 01:00:49.775
Marry me, baby.

01:00:49.812 --> 01:00:53.373
- Be my wife.
- What?

01:00:53.415 --> 01:00:56.441
I'm serious.
Let's do it.

01:00:56.485 --> 01:01:00.819
I'm sorry.
You're asking me to marry you?

01:01:00.856 --> 01:01:02.847
Yes.

01:01:18.507 --> 01:01:20.498
So?

01:01:24.079 --> 01:01:27.071
- You want to marry me?
- Totally.

01:01:27.116 --> 01:01:29.084
Marriage.

01:01:35.691 --> 01:01:39.593
- I'm not buying it.
- What?

01:01:39.628 --> 01:01:42.392
- There's something off about this.
- Wait, what are you talking about?

01:01:43.532 --> 01:01:47.229
Did you... did this just occur to you,
like, 60 seconds ago?

01:01:47.269 --> 01:01:48.531
- "Let's get married"?
- No.

01:01:48.570 --> 01:01:51.095
I've been giving it
a lot of thought

01:01:51.140 --> 01:01:54.041
and I think we should do it.

01:01:54.076 --> 01:01:58.479
Uh-huh.
You got a, you know, ring?

01:02:00.582 --> 01:02:02.447
Well, I will.

01:02:02.484 --> 01:02:05.351
I mean you will... get one.

01:02:05.387 --> 01:02:08.550
I didn't know you'd be
a stickler for protocol.

01:02:08.590 --> 01:02:10.751
Come on, Mary Catherine,

01:02:10.792 --> 01:02:13.283
we're not those people.

01:02:13.328 --> 01:02:14.818
Just say yes.

01:02:14.863 --> 01:02:16.694
